# Loops Within Loops

You can put any loop inside another loop. Useful for working with multi-dimensional data.

Example: Multiplication table.

```php
for ($i = 1; $i <= 3; $i++) {
    for ($j = 1; $j <= 3; $j++) {
        echo "$i x $j = " . ($i * $j) . "\n";
    }
}
```

```php
<?php
$matrix = [
    [1, 2, 3],
    [4, 5, 6],
    [7, 8, 9]
];

foreach ($matrix as $row) {
    foreach ($row as $value) {
        echo $value . " ";
    }
    echo "\n";
}
// Output:
// 1 2 3 
// 4 5 6 
// 7 8 9 
?>
```

